===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# {{lb|en|uncountable}} A black rock formed from [[prehistoric]] plant [[remains]], composed largely of [[carbon]] and burned as a fuel.
# {{lb|en|countable}} A piece of coal used for burning. Note that in British English either of the following examples could be used, whereas the latter would be more common in American English.
#: ''Put some '''coals''' on the fire.''
#: ''Put some '''coal''' on the fire.''
# {{lb|en|countable}} A type of coal, such as [[bituminous]], [[anthracite]], or [[lignite]], and grades and varieties thereof.
# {{lb|en|countable}} A glowing or charred piece of coal, wood, or other solid fuel.
#: ''Just as the camp-fire died down to just '''coals''', with no flames to burn the marshmallows, someone dumped a whole load of wood on, so I gave up and went to bed.''
# [[charcoal|Charcoal]].

